00:53:41.000 --> 00:53:45.120
[Amit Varma]: Society and what you're talking about this transactional model and these rituals that

00:53:45.120 --> 00:53:50.240
[Amit Varma]: you perform again, I'll quote from your book, because I just found this an incredibly fascinating

00:53:50.240 --> 00:53:54.640
[Amit Varma]: and jaw dropping quote, or stop quote, four kinds of membership were on offer for the

00:53:54.640 --> 00:53:55.920
[Amit Varma]: Gita department.

00:53:55.920 --> 00:54:01.560
[Amit Varma]: The first included those who read the entire Gita 18 chapters once every day, 365 times

00:54:01.560 --> 00:54:02.560
[Amit Varma]: in a year.

00:54:02.560 --> 00:54:06.600
[Amit Varma]: The second type of members could finish all the chapters over two days, and the complete

00:54:06.600 --> 00:54:08.560
[Amit Varma]: text 180 times in a year.

00:54:08.560 --> 00:54:14.480
[Amit Varma]: The third category of members read six chapters in a day, thus reading the Gita 120 times

00:54:14.480 --> 00:54:15.480
[Amit Varma]: in a year.

00:54:15.480 --> 00:54:19.200
[Amit Varma]: The last category of members could reach as much of the Gita as they wish daily, as long

00:54:19.200 --> 00:54:23.720
[Amit Varma]: as they completed at least 42 readings in a year, stop quote.

00:54:23.720 --> 00:54:28.440
[Amit Varma]: And it's fascinating, you don't need to live a virtuous life, you don't need to just read

00:54:28.440 --> 00:54:30.440
